ğŸ§  what is ngnix 
  Nginx is a high-performance web server and reverse proxy used to efficiently serve and manage web traffic.

Client request à¤­à¥‡à¤œà¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ
Nginx config check à¤•à¤°à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ
à¤…à¤—à¤° static file à¤¹à¥ˆ â†’ direct serve
à¤…à¤—à¤° backend à¤šà¤¾à¤¹à¤¿à¤ â†’ proxy_pass
à¤…à¤—à¤° multiple backend à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ â†’ load balance
Fast event-driven mechanism à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¤œà¤¾à¤°à¥‹à¤‚ requests handle à¤•à¤°à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ

why we use Nginx		

Load Balancing
Direct access = single server overload.
Reverse proxy distributes traffic across multiple backend servers.

High Availability
If one backend fails, reverse proxy redirects traffic to healthy servers.
Direct exposure has no failover.

Performance
App servers are slow at handling thousands of connections.
Reverse proxy (NGINX) handles connections efficiently and forwards only valid requests.

