ğŸ§  A container keeps restarting in production. How do you debug it?
   I check the container/pod status and events, then review current and previous logs to find the crash reason.
   Next, I verify resource limits, health probes, and configuration to fix whatâ€™s causing the restarts.

   â€œCrashLoopBackOff = app issueâ€
CrashLoopBackOff occurs when a container repeatedly crashes after starting, commonly due to application errors, misconfiguration, or resource limits.
Verify container command & entrypoint
Check missing environment variables
Verify ConfigMap and Secret mounts
Fix liveness/readiness probes      ## Wrong port in probe, App starting slowly(Increase startup delay)
Check OOMKilled and increase memory limits
Delete pod to restart: kubectl delete pod <pod-name>

kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
kubectl logs <pod-name>
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous

From the output:
If OOMKilled â†’ increase memory limits
If probe failed â†’ fix probe or increase delays
it may be a configMap error secrets error

