ğŸ§  How do you troubleshoot â€œpermission deniedâ€ inside container?
File or directory permissions
The containerâ€™s process user does not have access to a file or folder.
Example: trying to write to /data as a non-root user.

Executing scripts without execute permission
./start.sh
If the script is not executable â†’ permission denied

How to troubleshoot

1ï¸âƒ£ Check permissions inside the container
ls -l /path/to/file

2ï¸âƒ£ Change ownership or permissions
chown -R myuser:myuser /app/data
chmod +x /app/start.sh

4ï¸âƒ£ Set correct user in Dockerfile
USER myuser

